            <Attribute name="Description" type="String">
                <Value>The (Application Mode) Stellar Centroid Data Packet contains reported Stellar-Side Centroids, which are part of the core LRS data output.  This packet is normally reported and stored at a nominally 10 Hz rate with a variable number of stars reported and is available through all data channels (SSR, real time telemetry, and onboard to the spacecraft ACS).</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="data_rate" type="String">
                <Value>Data within this group are stored at the data rate of the source LRS Stellar Centroid Data Packet. (nominally 10 per second.)</Value>
            </Attribute>
        </Group>
        <Group name="hk_1120">
            <Dimension name="delta_time" size="423"/>
            <Float64 name="delta_time">
                <Dim name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>Elapsed GPS seconds</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="standard_name" type="String">
                    <Value>time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>seconds since 2018-01-01</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>Derived via Time Tagging</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>Number of GPS seconds since the ATLAS SDP epoch. The ATLAS Standard Data Products (SDP) epoch offset is defined within /ancillary_data/atlas_sdp_gps_epoch as the number of GPS seconds between the GPS epoch (1980-01-06T00:00:00.000000Z UTC) and the ATLAS SDP epoch. By adding the offset contained within atlas_sdp_gps_epoch to delta time parameters, the time in gps_seconds relative to the GPS epoch can be computed.</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                    <Value>latitude longitude</Value>
                </Attribute>
            </Float64>
            <Float32 name="srate_y">
                <Dim name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK Stellar Pattern Rate  Y</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>pixels/second</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>Y component (tip/tilt) of the stellar rate pattern estimate</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                    <Value>delta_time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Map name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
            </Float32>
            <Float32 name="pc_t">
                <Dim name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK Processor Card Thermistor</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>degreesC</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>Temperature of Processor Card - 0x0000 = 0.000 V (nominal short;) 0xFFFF = +4.000 V (nominal open) [see thermistor scaling section later for temperature scaling]</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                    <Value>delta_time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Map name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
            </Float32>
            <UInt32 name="spwdiscardlink">
                <Dim name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK Spacewire tlm packets dropped due to link not available</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>counts</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>This 32-bit counter is incremented every time a spacewire telemetry packet is dropped by Failsafe Mode while waiting for a valid spacewire link between the LRS and MEB (an abnormal condition).  It starts at 0x00000000, and rolls over to 0x00000000 when it increments from 0xFFFFFFFF.  This counter will be reset at power on and by a Failsafe Reset Counters Command (LRSfscmRSTCNT).</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                    <Value>delta_time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Map name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
            </UInt32>
            <Int8 name="sysstat_ac_en">
                <Dim name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK System Status Register - Analog Converter Status</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>1</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="valid_min" type="Int8">
                    <Value>0</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="valid_max" type="Int8">
                    <Value>1</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>The current status of the LRS FPGA Analog Converter. (0 =DISABLED (abnormal condition); 1 = ENABLED (normal operating condition))</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                    <Value>delta_time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="flag_meanings" type="String">
                    <Value>disabled enabled</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="flag_values" type="Int8">
                    <Value>0</Value>
                    <Value>1</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Map name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
            </Int8>
            <UInt16 name="timecnt">
                <Dim name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK Valid Time Sync Command Counter</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>counts</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>The Valid Time Sync Command Counter is a 16-bit counter that increments each time that the Failsafe Mode processes a valid command of the corresponding command type.  A valid command is defined as a command that passes all verification tests.  The counter starts at 0x0000, and rolls over to 0x0000 when it increments from 0xFFFF.  The counter is reset at power on and by a Failsafe Reset Counters Command (LRSfscmRSTCNT).</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                    <Value>delta_time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Map name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
            </UInt16>
            <Float32 name="m12v_ldc_mon_v">
                <Dim name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK -12VDC LDC Monitor</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>volts</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>Voltage of -12VDC LDC Monitor - 0x0000 = 0.000 V; 0xBF9D = -12.000 V (nominal value); 0xFFFF = -16.000 V : A_LRS_HK.ANALOGHK[11]</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                    <Value>delta_time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Map name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
            </Float32>
            <UInt16 name="timeerrcnt">
                <Dim name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK Time Sync Command Error Counter</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>counts</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>The 16-bit Time Sync Command error Counter is incremented every time the Failsafe Mode has one or more command verification or processing errors with the corresponding command type (abnormal conditions).  The counter starts at 0x0000, and rolls over to 0x0000 when it increments from 0xFFFF.  The counter increments only once per command when there is at least one verification/processing error for that command.  TIMEERRCODE will indicate the type of error.  The counter is reset at power on and by a Failsafe Reset Counters Command (LRSfscmRSTCNT).</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                    <Value>delta_time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Map name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
            </UInt16>
            <Float32 name="p5v_sdc_mon_v">
                <Dim name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK +5VDC SDC Monitor</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>volts</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>Voltage of +5VDC SDC Monitor - 0x0000 = 0.000 V; 0xA000 = +5.000 V (nominal value); 0xFFFF = +8.000 V : A_LRS_HK.ANALOGHK[13]</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                    <Value>delta_time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Map name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
            </Float32>
            <UInt16 name="cmderrcode">
                <Dim name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK Unique Code for User Command Errors</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>counts</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>LRS_HK</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>The 16-bit Command Error Unique Code indicates the last type of command error that occurred in Failsafe Mode.  This code will be reset at power on and by a Failsafe Reset Counters Command (LRSfscmRSTCNT).  The error codes are defined in Table 19: Command Validation Error Codes in the LRS command and data ICD.</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                    <Value>delta_time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Map name="/lrs/hk_1120/delta_time"/>
            </UInt16>
