                </Attribute>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="Description" type="String">
                <Value>Contains parameters relating to the Application Housekeeping Packet (LRStmHK)(APID 1120). The (Application Mode) Housekeeping Packet provides all LRS health and safety data.  It is normally reported and stored at a 1 Hz rate.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="data_rate" type="String">
                <Value>Data within this group are stored at the data rate of the source LRS Housekeeping Data (nominally once per second).</Value>
            </Attribute>
        </Group>
    </Group>
    <Group name="orbit_info">
        <Dimension name="delta_time" size="1"/>
        <Float64 name="delta_time">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/delta_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Granule Start Time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="standard_name" type="String">
                <Value>time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>seconds since 2018-01-01</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>Operations</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>Number of GPS seconds since the ATLAS SDP epoch at the start of the granule. At the time of ATL02 creation, the equator crossing time is not precisely known.. The ATLAS Standard Data Products (SDP) epoch offset is defined within /ancillary_data/atlas_sdp_gps_epoch as the number of GPS seconds between the GPS epoch (1980-01-06T00:00:00.000000Z UTC) and the ATLAS SDP epoch. By adding the offset contained within atlas_sdp_gps_epoch to delta time parameters, the time in gps_seconds relative to the GPS epoch can be computed.</Value>
            </Attribute>
        </Float64>
        <Int8 name="cycle_number">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/delta_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Cycle Number</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_min" type="Int8">
                <Value>0</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_max" type="Int8">
                <Value>50</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>A count of the number of exact repeats of this reference orbit.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                <Value>delta_time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>Operations</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Map name="/orbit_info/delta_time"/>
        </Int8>
        <UInt16 name="orbit_number">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/delta_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Orbit Number</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_min" type="UInt16">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_max" type="UInt16">
                <Value>65000</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>Unique identifying number for each planned ICESat-2 orbit.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                <Value>delta_time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>Operations</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Map name="/orbit_info/delta_time"/>
        </UInt16>
        <Int16 name="rgt">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/delta_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Reference Ground track</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>Operations</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_min" type="Int16">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_max" type="Int16">
                <Value>1387</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>The reference ground track (RGT) is the track on the earth at which a specified unit vector within the observatory is pointed. Under nominal operating conditions, there will be no data collected along the RGT, as the RGT is spanned by GT3 and GT4.  During slews or off-pointing, it is possible that ground tracks may intersect the RGT. The ICESat-2 mission has 1387 RGTs.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                <Value>delta_time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Map name="/orbit_info/delta_time"/>
        </Int16>
        <Attribute name="DODS_EXTRA" type="Container">
            <Attribute name="Unlimited_Dimension" type="String">
                <Value>delta_time</Value>
            </Attribute>
        </Attribute>
        <Attribute name="Description" type="String">
            <Value>Contains orbit information.</Value>
        </Attribute>
        <Attribute name="data_rate" type="String">
            <Value>Data within this group are stored at the data rate of the source PCE Altimetric Data Packets. (nominally fifty per second.)</Value>
        </Attribute>
    </Group>
    <Group name="quality_assessment">
        <Dimension name="ds_statistics" size="5"/>
        <Int8 name="ds_statistics">
            <Dim name="/quality_assessment/ds_statistics"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Dimension scale for QA statistics</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>Derived (QA)</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>qualityInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>QA statistics array index</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="flag_meanings" type="String">
                <Value>number_of_points minimum maximum average standard_deviation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="flag_values" type="Int8">
                <Value>1</Value>
                <Value>2</Value>
                <Value>3</Value>
                <Value>4</Value>
                <Value>5</Value>
            </Attribute>
        </Int8>
        <Int32 name="qa_granule_fail_reason">
            <Dim size="1"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Granule Failure Reason</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_min" type="Int32">
                <Value>0</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_max" type="Int32">
                <Value>5</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>qualityInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>Flag indicating granule failure reason. 0=no failure; 1=processing error; 2=Insufficient output data was generated; 3=An uncorrected TxRx slip condition was detected; 4=TBD_Failure; 5=other failure.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="flag_meanings" type="String">
                <Value>no_failure NO_SIM_HK NO_PMF_TIME TIME_OF_DAY_FAILURE TIME_OF_FLIGHT_FAILURE OTHER_FAILURE</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="flag_values" type="Int32">
                <Value>0</Value>
                <Value>1</Value>
                <Value>2</Value>
                <Value>3</Value>
                <Value>4</Value>
                <Value>5</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>Operations</Value>
            </Attribute>
        </Int32>
        <Int32 name="qa_granule_pass_fail">
            <Dim size="1"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Granule Pass Flag</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_min" type="Int32">
                <Value>0</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_max" type="Int32">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>qualityInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>Flag indicating granule quality. 0=granule passes automatic QA. 1=granule fails automatic QA.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="flag_meanings" type="String">
                <Value>PASS FAIL</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="flag_values" type="Int32">
                <Value>0</Value>
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>Operations</Value>
            </Attribute>
        </Int32>
        <Attribute name="Description" type="String">
            <Value>Contains quality assessment data. This may include QA counters, QA along-track data and/or QA summary data.</Value>
        </Attribute>
        <Attribute name="DODS_EXTRA" type="Container">
            <Attribute name="Unlimited_Dimension" type="String">
                <Value>ds_statistics</Value>
            </Attribute>
        </Attribute>
        <Group name="along_track">
            <Dimension name="delta_time_start" size="43"/>
            <Float64 name="delta_time_start">
                <Dim name="/quality_assessment/along_track/delta_time_start"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>Elapsed UTC seconds</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="standard_name" type="String">
                    <Value>time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>seconds since 2018-01-01</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>Derived via Time Tagging</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>Number of seconds since the ATLAS SDP epoch at the start of the QA interval. The ATLAS Standard Data Products (SDP) epoch offset is defined within /ancillary_data/atlas_sdp_gps_epoch as the number of GPS seconds between the GPS epoch (1980-01-06T00:00:00.000000Z UTC) and the ATLAS SDP epoch. By adding the offset contained within atlas_sdp_gps_epoch to delta time parameters, the time in gps_seconds relative to the GPS epoch can be computed.</Value>
                </Attribute>
            </Float64>
            <Float64 name="delta_time_end">
                <Dim name="/quality_assessment/along_track/delta_time_start"/>
                <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                    <Value>Elapsed GPS seconds</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="standard_name" type="String">
                    <Value>time</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                    <Value>seconds since 2018-01-01</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                    <Value>Derived via Time Tagging</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>Number of seconds since the ATLAS SDP epoch at the end of the QA interval. The ATLAS Standard Data Products (SDP) epoch offset is defined within /ancillary_data/atlas_sdp_gps_epoch as the number of GPS seconds between the GPS epoch (1980-01-06T00:00:00.000000Z UTC) and the ATLAS SDP epoch. By adding the offset contained within atlas_sdp_gps_epoch to delta time parameters, the time in gps_seconds relative to the GPS epoch can be computed.</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Map name="/quality_assessment/along_track/delta_time_start"/>
            </Float64>
            <Attribute name="DODS_EXTRA" type="Container">
                <Attribute name="Unlimited_Dimension" type="String">
                    <Value>delta_time_start</Value>
                </Attribute>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="Description" type="String">
                <Value>Along-track statistics</Value>
            </Attribute>
