                    <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
                </Attribute>
                <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                    <Value>The time tag of the data computed from raw_acs_time_sec and subseconds in the L1A Attitude_control_ group, relative to the ATLAS SDP epoch. The ATLAS Standard Data Products (SDP) epoch offset is defined within /ancillary_data/atlas_sdp_gps_epoch as the number of GPS seconds between the GPS epoch (1980-01-06T00:00:00.000000Z UTC) and the ATLAS SDP epoch. By adding the offset contained within atlas_sdp_gps_epoch to delta time parameters, the time in gps_seconds relative to the GPS epoch can be computed.</Value>
