          &lt;/gmd:citation&gt;
          &lt;!-- ECS extracts the CollectionDescription from here --&gt;
          &lt;gmd:abstract&gt;
            &lt;gco:CharacterString&gt;ATL02 Science unit converted time ordered telemetry calibrated for instrument effects.  All photon events per beam per shot.  Includes atmosphere raw profiles, housekeeping data, engineering data, s/c position, and pointing data.&lt;/gco:CharacterString&gt;
          &lt;/gmd:abstract&gt;
          &lt;gmd:purpose&gt;
            &lt;gco:CharacterString&gt;The purpose of ATL02 is to provide science-unit, calibrated data for upstream processing. Data converted from raw counts to science units, calibrated for instrument effects and precisely time-tagged. ATL02 provides the position and pointing data needed to precisely geolocate each photon. ATL02 is of limited use to the science community.&lt;/gco:CharacterString&gt;
          &lt;/gmd:purpose&gt;
          &lt;gmd:credit&gt;
            &lt;gco:CharacterString&gt;The software that generates the ATL02 product was designed and implemented at the NASA Wallops Flight Facility in Wallops Island, Virginia.&lt;/gco:CharacterString&gt;
          &lt;/gmd:credit&gt;
          &lt;gmd:status&gt;
            &lt;gmd:MD_ProgressCode codeList=&quot;http://www.isotc211.org/2005/resources/Codelist/gmxCodelists.xml#MD_ProgressCode&quot; codeListValue=&quot;onGoing&quot;&gt;onGoing&lt;/gmd:MD_ProgressCode&gt;
          &lt;/gmd:status&gt;
