            <Attribute name="resourceProviderOrganizationName" type="String">
                <Value>National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA)</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="abstract" type="String">
                <Value>ATL02 Science unit converted time ordered telemetry calibrated for instrument effects.  All photon events per beam per shot.  Includes atmosphere raw profiles, housekeeping data, engineering data, s/c position, and pointing data.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="purpose" type="String">
                <Value>The purpose of ATL02 is to provide science-unit, calibrated data for upstream processing. Data converted from raw counts to science units, calibrated for instrument effects and precisely time-tagged. ATL02 provides the position and pointing data needed to precisely geolocate each photon. ATL02 is of limited use to the science community.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="credit" type="String">
                <Value>The software that generates the ATL02 product was designed and implemented at the NASA Wallops Flight Facility in Wallops Island, Virginia.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="status" type="String">
                <Value>onGoing</Value>
            </Attribute>
